Hey, Gonda.

263
00:13:35.680 --> 00:13:38.930
Why do you want to get married so badly?

264
00:13:41.130 --> 00:13:46.260
Mengyomen Ramen

265
00:13:41.130 --> 00:13:46.260
Open

266
00:13:41.390 --> 00:13:43.990
Is it weird to want to get married?

267
00:13:43.990 --> 00:13:48.490
Well, not many people around me do.

268
00:13:48.970 --> 00:13:52.480
You know, I was poor when I was a kid.

269
00:13:52.480 --> 00:13:55.530
Oh, please don't tell Keisuke-san about this.

270
00:13:55.530 --> 00:13:57.850
He'll turn anything into a joke.

271
00:13:57.850 --> 00:13:59.110
S-Sure.

272
00:14:00.080 --> 00:14:02.540
My father was a little problematic.

273
00:14:02.540 --> 00:14:05.950
He was in loads of debt, and 
all my parents did was fight.

274
00:14:06.360 --> 00:14:08.950
My big brother and I were close, though.

275
00:14:08.950 --> 00:14:12.350
I don't have many good childhood memories.

276
00:14:08.950 --> 00:14:12.830
Full-Color Field Guide 
to Japanese Fungi

277
00:14:13.000 --> 00:14:17.340
I ate lots of ramen and such 
back then, and now I love it.

278
00:14:17.340 --> 00:14:18.500
You eat too much.

279
00:14:18.890 --> 00:14:21.740
I was a big dummy who was no good at school,

280
00:14:21.740 --> 00:14:24.350
but thankfully I managed to land a job.

281
00:14:24.890 --> 00:14:27.240
My brother works for the government.

282
00:14:27.240 --> 00:14:28.790
Not bad, huh?

283
00:14:30.050 --> 00:14:34.940
I guess that's why I yearn for 
a proper home life or something.

284
00:14:35.220 --> 00:14:37.690
It doesn't have to be anything special,

285
00:14:37.690 --> 00:14:41.740
but I want to marry someone I love, 
be blessed with some cute kids,

286
00:14:41.740 --> 00:14:43.690
and enjoy life.

287
00:14:44.200 --> 00:14:47.870
I have a feeling I could do that with Kaori.

288
00:14:48.700 --> 00:14:53.390
Having kids would be great. 
I'd be such a loving father.

289
00:14:53.390 --> 00:14:57.730
You have some romantic ideas, 
which surprises me.

290
00:14:57.730 --> 00:14:59.690
I said it because it's you, Master!

291
00:14:59.690 --> 00:15:02.080
It must sound gross, coming 
from a guy who looks like me.

292
00:15:02.080 --> 00:15:03.840
Yeah, I could never hope to...

293
00:15:03.840 --> 00:15:05.550
Give it a shot, Gonda.

294
00:15:06.050 --> 00:15:07.490
I've got your back.

295
00:15:07.490 --> 00:15:09.150
Oh yeah, you bet.

296
00:15:09.150 --> 00:15:10.610
I'm gonna do it.

297
00:15:14.520 --> 00:15:16.690
<i>Gon-chan, what's up?</i>

298
00:15:16.690 --> 00:15:19.330
Kaori, could we meet up now?

299
00:15:19.330 --> 00:15:23.810
<i>Tonight? Sorry, weekdays are no good for me.</i>

300
00:15:23.810 --> 00:15:26.450
Please! The sooner the better.

301
00:15:26.450 --> 00:15:30.040
<i>Well, okay, if it's quick.</i>

302
00:15:31.410 --> 00:15:32.810
Thanks for waiting, Gon-chan.

303
00:15:34.780 --> 00:15:35.960
What's wrong?

304
00:15:37.420 --> 00:15:41.490
Kaori, let's date and eventually get married!

305
00:15:51.730 --> 00:15:54.410
Do you mean that?

306
00:15:54.410 --> 00:15:56.430
Of course I do! Of course.

307
00:16:05.930 --> 00:16:08.110
Gon-chan, come with me.

308
00:16:29.400 --> 00:16:31.970
Oh, Ema-san. Hello.

309
00:16:31.970 --> 00:16:34.930
Sorry I'm a little late.

310
00:16:34.930 --> 00:16:38.060
Mok-kun, look who's here for you.

311
00:16:38.560 --> 00:16:41.310
Tokyo Certified 
Day Care

312
00:16:38.560 --> 00:16:41.310
Takenoko Kids

313
00:16:41.310 --> 00:16:43.820
Certified Day Care

314
00:17:01.540 --> 00:17:05.710
Working while raising a child isn't easy.

315
00:17:06.670 --> 00:17:09.310
Gon-chan, you still mean it?

316
00:17:09.310 --> 00:17:11.480
Because I'm a single mother.

317
00:17:20.420 --> 00:17:22.600
It's okay, don't force yourself.

318
00:17:24.090 --> 00:17:25.780
See ya, Gon-chan.

319
00:17:32.570 --> 00:17:35.330
Deep Sea Bar

320
00:17:33.680 --> 00:17:35.330
Single mother?

321
00:17:35.850 --> 00:17:38.030
It doesn't bother me at all.

322
00:17:38.030 --> 00:17:41.410
I-I might have panicked for a moment, though.

323
00:17:41.410 --> 00:17:43.740
So, what'll you do?

324
00:17:45.720 --> 00:17:47.840
What'll I do? Well...

325
00:17:56.200 --> 00:18:00.400
<i>I've got to talk to Kaori again.</i>

326
00:18:01.600 --> 00:18:04.100
Bank

327
00:18:06.860 --> 00:18:09.860
Deposits made via other firms are listed 
in the description box, and the date on
 which they are payable is displayed on
 the corresponding line.
 Furthermore, the exact time a deposit
 is payable varies depending on the type
 of firm involved. Please ask a teller for
 details.

328
00:18:08.460 --> 00:18:11.160
<i>I can afford to support a child.</i>

329
00:18:11.160 --> 00:18:12.280
Gonda-san.

330
00:18:12.810 --> 00:18:15.070
You seem kind of down today.

331
00:18:15.070 --> 00:18:17.030
N-Nothing's wrong.

332
00:18:17.030 --> 00:18:18.630
No? Okay.

333
00:18:25.290 --> 00:18:26.040
See ya

334
00:18:25.290 --> 00:18:26.040
Today

335
00:18:25.290 --> 00:18:26.040
Kaori, sorry about the other day!

336
00:18:26.040 --> 00:18:26.790
Today

337
00:18:26.040 --> 00:18:26.790
Kaori, sorry about the other day!

338
00:18:26.040 --> 00:18:26.790
I'd like you to hear me out
 one more time.

339
00:18:26.790 --> 00:18:29.300
I'd like you to hear me out
 one more time.

340
00:18:26.790 --> 00:18:29.300
I'm waiting at the restaurant where
 we looked at pics together!!

341
00:18:39.640 --> 00:18:42.230
You can get drinks over there.

342
00:18:42.230 --> 00:18:44.240
Sure, thanks.

343
00:18:46.060 --> 00:18:48.570
Overall Account Bankbook

344
00:18:46.060 --> 00:18:48.570
Gonda Hiromi

345
00:18:53.250 --> 00:18:57.370
<i>Kaori sure was affectionate with her kid.</i>

346
00:18:59.380 --> 00:19:02.590
<i>What look did I have on my face back then?</i>

347
00:19:04.420 --> 00:19:05.620
<i>Kaori...</i>

348
00:19:09.290 --> 00:19:10.660
Gon-chan?

349
00:19:14.470 --> 00:19:15.550
Gon-chan?

350
00:19:15.980 --> 00:19:17.830
Y-Yes.

351
00:19:17.830 --> 00:19:20.050
You look just like she described you.

352
00:19:20.960 --> 00:19:24.310
I'm Ichika, a friend of Kaori's.

353
00:19:25.140 --> 00:19:26.150
Her friend?

354
00:19:26.150 --> 00:19:29.720
Right. She and I use the same day care.

355
00:19:29.720 --> 00:19:32.940
And so, Kaori said she couldn't come today.

356
00:19:33.260 --> 00:19:34.670
I'm sorry.

357
00:19:36.830 --> 00:19:39.710
I have a message from her.

358
00:19:39.710 --> 00:19:41.570
She said, "Don't worry about it."

359
00:19:44.950 --> 00:19:47.930
She also said, "Thank you."

360
00:19:48.720 --> 00:19:52.100
Does she not like me anymore?

361
00:19:52.100 --> 00:19:52.840
Huh?

362
00:19:53.580 --> 00:19:55.720
I'm not really sure.

363
00:19:55.720 --> 00:19:58.590
Were the two of you dating?

364
00:19:58.890 --> 00:20:02.790
No, it wasn't like that. Uh...

365
00:20:02.790 --> 00:20:04.100
But listen, Gon-chan.

366
00:20:04.360 --> 00:20:07.350
It's a big decision, letting 
someone meet your kid.

367
00:20:07.860 --> 00:20:11.060
I'd use my kid to scare away 
a guy who won't take a hint,

368
00:20:11.060 --> 00:20:13.830
but Kaori's not that sort of person.

369
00:20:16.820 --> 00:20:19.320
Overall Account Bankbook

370
00:20:16.820 --> 00:20:19.320
Gonda Hiromi

371
00:20:20.860 --> 00:20:22.540
Sorry, Gon-chan.

372
00:20:24.550 --> 00:20:27.080
I guess it's not my place to say.

373
00:20:35.720 --> 00:20:40.810
Master, I'm going to stop talking 
about marriage and stuff.

374
00:20:41.760 --> 00:20:44.330
When it comes to marriage, I was all talk.

375
00:20:44.860 --> 00:20:47.350
I wasn't ready at all.

376
00:20:48.810 --> 00:20:51.850
I doubt anyone can be ready for that stuff.

377
00:20:57.100 --> 00:21:02.040
Kaori had faith in me, and I flinched.

378
00:21:02.040 --> 00:21:04.040
I really regret it.

379
00:21:05.990 --> 00:21:10.370
I went and hurt Kaori's feelings.

380
00:21:11.040 --> 00:21:14.130
I'm the worst!

381
00:21:18.690 --> 00:21:22.530
<i>No, Gonda. You're amazing.</i>

382
00:21:23.200 --> 00:21:24.790
<i>Truly amazing.</i>

383
00:21:26.130 --> 00:21:28.950
<i>Have I ever taken Honjoji-san 
into consideration this much?</i>

384
00:21:29.390 --> 00:21:32.270
<i>Enough to move me to tears?</i>

